  You are exactly correct.   The mods at SOE's boards are all about damage control plain and simple.  They remove posts that say anything negative UNLESS it gets immediate community response on their boards...such things as that can be affected by any number of things like Time-Zone differences, holidays, average work schedule of a populace, etc.  
<br />
   Only on a commnity run board(and they should do their best to visit as many community boards for each class as possible..not  just one community bard site, but others to) can they find what players truly think.  The mods at SOE shelter and dull their view of us by erasing &quot;inciteful&quot; posts.  Here they can get to read directly what we think of their content, and what the problem is...not hear it from someone who gets payed minimum wage to browse a company web-site for info and translate the info....
<br />
  Personally I think them coming here to post would be way better than putting the weight of community issues on the shoulders of 1 or 2 or 3 people.  But in the case that they ever do come here we must strive not to sensor ourselves or become overly biased in an attempt to garner &quot;favor&quot;.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
