				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: More<a name="51214"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 11 04 12:39 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Folks, I was one of the contributors to that list.  It was a collection of a lot of posts.  It started with a bit thread full of idea posts.  Then Ash started another thread to get all the ideas whittled down to 10.  
<br />

<br />
Here it is http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=bardbalance&amp;message.id=177
<br />

<br />
Then  she posted a top 10, and that got rearranged and modified.  
<br />

<br />
Here is the top 10 discussion thread: http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=bardbalance&amp;message.id=271&amp;view=by_date_ascending&amp;page=1
<br />

<br />
After some discussion, our class issues came down to this top 10:
<br />

<br />
1 - More over all items with modifiers (weapons and instruments) (14)
<br />
2- Lower the Fizzle Rate (14)
<br />
3 - Add in-game twisting function or macros
<br />
4- Raise Melee DPS back to 65% of a warrior (12)
<br />
5 - More type 7/8 instrument augments (LDoN points/ GoD drops, mod must be 1.8+) for placement on armor. (7)
<br />
6 - Better AA’s and Songs (7) 
<br />
Add offensive AA's and disciplines (11)
<br />
7 - Increase Puretone's usefulness
<br />
8 - Better Mitigation
<br />
9 - Make Songblade Inventory Clickable (7)
<br />
10 - The modifer cap 
<br />

<br />
I argued hard for items 2, 3, 6, 7, and 10.  If you have issues with any of these, read my posts that are on that board and take them up there.  
<br />

<br />
Now there was plenty of discord over this list, but it was a decently fair approximation of the discussions that had taken place up to that point.  
<br />

<br />
That's the story of how our top 10 came into being.  Everyone who has an active account had opportunities in 3 seperate threads to contribute to the discussion.  I wish there had been more discussion over it, but Ash was on a deadline, and we got to a point where it was the same people rehashing the same arguments.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
