				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: SoE's Response to Bard Top 10 Issues<a name="51218"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 11 04 12:49 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Sadiki, I was one of the people asking for an autotwisting feature in-game.  There was and is a good deal of contraversy over it.  
<br />

<br />
Essentially, those who argue for it say that the medical problems that come with twisting are bad, that twisting takes no skill or sense of timing, now that we have a casting bar, that hotkeying songs to ease up the strain of twisting makes your hotkey bank fill up way too much, that twisting is not fun, that picking the right songs to twist is what makes a good bard good, and that they have already authorized autotwisting 3rd-party hardware.
<br />

<br />
Those who are against having an autotwist feature worry that it will take all the challenge out of playing a bard, and turn us into macrobots.
<br />

<br />
Say what you may, but it seems the majority of the folks who posted were in favor of an in-game autotwist feature.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
